Description: Title-page to George Sandys, 'A Relation of a Journey begun An: Dom: 1610' (London, W. Barrett, 1621); title in centre; above, in an oval, the Ascension, between figures representing 'Veritas' and 'Constantia'; either side of title emblematic figures representing Turkey ('Achmet, sive Tyrannus') and Egypt ('Isis, sive Ægyptus'); below, the Cumaean Sibyl flanked by Mary Magdalene and a bull ('Apis sive Osyris'). Engraving
Bibliographic references: Hind 1952-64 / Engraving in England in the Sixteenth and Seventeenth Centuries (II.238.43)
Associated titles: A Relation of a Journey begun An: Dom: 1610
